1. rails new my_project_name -G --database=postgresql
2. rails db:create #creates database 
3. rails db:setup ##runs rails db:create, rails db:migrate then rails db:see
##make sure your postgresql server is running

rails c ## Rails Console. Use pry-rails gem
rails s ## activates active server for localhost & postman testing


other commands #unlikely to be useful for assessment but good to know
rails db:drop will drop the entire database off the server 
rails db:purge will keep the database loaded but it will be fresh & need to be re-migrated/seeded.